This is an extraordinary 47th floor corner apartment with a wide open south-facing and west-facing sun-filled view to match. Look through the floor-to-ceiling windows out on Lake Michigan, the Chicago River, the amazing Chicago skyline, the Hancock, the Trump, Willis (Sears) Tower, etc. Even stand by the west windows or on the balcony and look north out at North Avenue Beach and stretches of Lincoln Park. Daytime and nighttime views are simply breath-taking. Walk to multiple grocery stores, restaurants, the lakefront path (via the pedestrian path under Lake Shore Drive), Navy Pier, two AMC theaters, the Loop, Millennium Park, Grant Park, the Magnificent Mile, Red Line station, Northwestern Memorial Hospital, even the Art Institute, etc in this very safe and luxurious section of Chicago. Many bus lines are a few steps away, taxis are waiting 24/7 at the front door, and even indoor parking is an option.
The apartment is 1043 square feet, includes a balcony, in-unit washer/dryer, one full bath, one half bath, unusually ample closet space (three in the bedroom alone), building storage units optional, free bike storage, excellent building amenities (gym, party & game room, business center, outdoor pool, indoor resistance pool and jacuzzi, saunas, quiet study library, ATM, even a commercial Starbucks high end coffee machine at no extra charge), outstanding & responsive management and doormen. One cat is allowed at no additional cost; dogs strictly prohibited on this floor (per management). For more about the building amenities visit http://www.thestreeter.com/chicago-chicago-il/the-streeter/amenities/ and see what is offered. The apartment lay-out is such that the den could work as a second bedroom for a small child or two, i.e., someone not committed to the same level of privacy as an adult would be. The bathrooms and kitchen have ceramic tile flooring, the bedroom has carpet, and the remainder is wood laminate.
The apartment will be unfurnished, though some of the furniture would be available for sale if that makes it easier for you (quality queen bed & frame, two nightstands, 24" crt TV and stand, quality Crate & Barrel sofa, Wassily living room chair). The lease term is 4.5 months, $3600 per month, from October 1, 2014 through February 14, 2015. Parking is available through the management at an additional $195, payable to the management. Must have renters` insurance and show that to management. First and last (half) month rent are due on signing; the remaining three months` rent are due on the first of each of those months. (Keep in mind that the freight elevator must be reserved in advance for your move-in.) Cable TV and high speed Internet are included. Premium channels and electric are extra and must be arranged by you. Cleaning is available separately for approximately $65 per session, payable to the in-house cleaning woman. An application must be filled out either online or in-person in the on-site leasing office. The application includes a criminal background check and credit background check, and is usually completed in 24-48 hours.
We want to emphasize that this is "the apartment of a lifetime". You`ll cherish your time here. The neighbors are quiet and keep to themselves. We have to be out of Chicago for this period of time and worked with management here to make sure we could keep our dream apartment. We`re posting the ad a bit early for those of you who like to have details arranged in well in advance of your move.
